Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%labels
    Author ToyCI Builder
    Description Environment for Makefile-based CI/CD exercise

%post
    set -e

    # Refresh apt index and install required packages
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        make \
        python3 \
        python3-pip

    # Clean up apt caches to keep image small
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    # Install pytest for the grading harness
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare initial filesystem layout expected by the assignment
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Home base directory for the student
    mkdir -p /home/user/project
    # Make sure the student can write inside the project directory even if
    # UID/GID mapping differs at runtime
    chmod -R 0777 /home/user

    # Ensure the CI report does NOT exist at build time
    rm -f /home/user/project/ci_report.txt

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Put Python3 on PATH explicitly (usually already there, but safe)
    export PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:$PATH

%runscript
    echo "Container for Toy CI/CD assignment."
    echo "You probably want to 'exec' into the container and work under /home/user/project."

%help
    This container provides everything needed for the Toy CI/CD Makefile exercise:
    • GNU Make
    • Python 3
    • Pytest (used by the autograder)

    The project skeleton lives in /home/user/project.
    Start by adding a Makefile there, then run:
        make -C /home/user/project ci